## <a id='major-features'></a>New Features in Ops Manager v1.10.0

### <a id='bosh'></a>BOSH Updates

### <a id='api'></a>Ops Manager API

Operators can now use the API to automate more tasks, such as configuring tiles, uploading tiles, and fetching upgrades from Pivotal Network. 
To view the Ops Manager API documentation, browse to `https://YOUR-OPS-MANAGER-FQDN/docs`.

#### <a id='new-endpoints'></a>New Endpoints

The Ops Manager API has added the following endpoints:

* Operators can use an endpoint to assign a network and az to the director tile
* Operators can use an endpoint to get a staged cloud config
* Operator can use an endpoint to get a deployed cloud config 
* Operators can use a series of endpoints to rotate all their non configurable certificates
* Endpoint to list all certificate authorities
* Endpoint to add an OpsManager generated certificate authority 
* Endpoint to add a custom certificate authority 
* Endpoint to mark a certificate authority as Active
* Endpoint to regenerate all certificates using the Active certificate authority 
* Endpoint to delete Inactive certificate authorities 
* Lite Apply Changes Endpoint 

