#### <a id='certs'></a>Certificate Rotation


Ops Manager ships with a Certificate Authority (CA). This CA generates certificates that are used for communication across various PCF components. These certificates are non-configurable. 

Ops Manager now allows you to regenerate non-configurable TLS/SSL certs using the API. See the [Rotating Non-Configurable TLS/SSL Certificates](../../security/pcf-infrastructure/api-cert-rotation.html) topic for more information.

Ops Manager also allows operators to use an API endpoint to all their own custom CA authority. If added, this custom CA will be used to sign all non-configurable certificates and deployed across all relevant PCF components.

### <a id='sha2'></a>SHA-2

Previous versions of PCF used SHA-1 hashes, while PCF v1.10 uses SHA-2 by default. SHA-2 is available Both Operations Manager installations and certificates provided by PCF use SHA-2 hashes.

You cannot obtain SHA-2 by upgrading existing environments to PCF v1.10. Instead, you must perform a fresh install by following the steps in [Installing Pivotal Cloud Foundry](../installing/index.html).

